Two aspects of the structure of the brain make it difficult for us to transmit our feelings to animals.
On the one hand, the lateral prefrontal cortex is often connected with human awareness, the associated circuits (this is due to its direct participation in short memory and executive and control functions).
In man this wide zone is much more developed than in the other primates and it seems that among other creatures it is completely lacking.
