Repeated drivers of alcoholism will have to install the "alcolock"
The Ministry of the Interior requires drivers with three administrative penalties for excessive blood alcohol, install in his car the system that prevents driving the vehicle in a state of intoxication or if it does not blow into the device.
The measure was announced last June and is already included in the annual report of the State Attorney General, according to which it will be a one-year pilot project.
The purpose of this project is the reintegration of the driver, since he will have to attend a rehabilitation course on the road.
This initiative, in addition to the General Prosecutor for Road Safety, will be attended by the Directorate General of Traffic (DGT) and the Foundation Istituto Tecnologico per la Sicurezza del Automobile (FITSA).
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists reported more than once for driving while intoxicated then return to drive the car.
The alcoholock would avoid this, because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents you from starting the car if the driver does not blow, or when a higher concentration of alcohol is detected than allowed.
The cost is more than 1000 euros and would be borne by the sanctioned.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with such devices can reduce up to 65% of infringements committed during the first year of introduction.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people a year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to stop these behaviors before they become criminal offenses.
And to facilitate its development, since legal reform can be carried out on an ordinary basis, and undoubtedly the reform necessary for criminal procedure would require an organic law.
However, the device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial solution, although it has already been introduced experimentally in some commercial and public vehicles.
Just tomorrow, the Congress of Deputies will vote on an initiative of the PSOE in which it proposes to install this system in school buses, as has already been done in France.
