Paul Newman (1925-2008) - Death of a busy icon
The blue-eyed beauty was for a long time his ace in the sleeve, for others his weak point.
Did he get rid of the narcissistic mirror, the American actor with the spellbinding smile?
Yes and no.
His discretion, sensitivity and obvious talent would have expelled him from that circle of powerful consecrated to real sacred monsters.
What a constancy!
Paul Newman, who passed away on Friday at the age of 83 on his Connecticut ranch from lung cancer, remains one of the last American film icons of the years.
Less monumental than Brando, to whom he resembled and of whom he was for a long time a sort of rival on the screen, more cautious in his game, certainly more fragile, but also he spokesman for freedom and the development of dramatic convictions.
Mixed couples often give birth to magical children.
