The boxer Rocky Graziano, delinquent, tormented, violent, unforgettable in Up Somebody Loves Me, by Robert Wise, a role intended for James Dean and retaken after his death, which officially launched Newman in 1956.
That cute villain in the excellent Left, Oscar for best film in 1973.
