In the other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the manufacturing industry over the past year prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded those of last year by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among target groups of sectors, the largest monthly price increase occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer items prices increased by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sector prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
