Grapefruit juice was already under accusation because it was responsible for increasing the effects of certain antiarrhythmic drugs, antibiotics, anxiolytics, antihistamines and neurological drugs to levels considered toxic.
The same Italian Agency of the drug had reported in an information bulletin two years ago warning doctors and patients not to underestimate the danger arising from this mix and to pay attention to what you drink in case you take drugs such as Diazepam or Methadone.
